&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for a dynamic and enthusiastic Band 5 dietitian to join our friendly and supportive team at Wythenshawe Hospital to cover maternity leave on a 12 month&#39;s Fixed Term contract. This post is ideal for a newly qualified dietitian or someone seeking to broaden their experience in a variety of settings and specialities. We are a busy team of 27 dietitians and 2 dietetic assistants and will help you develop both your knowledge and skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Wythenshawe Hospital is part of Manchester Foundation Trust, one of the largest NHS Trusts in the UK and form part of a family of nine hospitals across six different sites. Our Trusts&#39; vision is to improve the health and quality of life of our diverse population that excels in quality, safety, patient experience, research, innovation and teaching. Wythenshawe hospital is a major acute teaching hospital and our fields of specialist expertise include cardiology and cardiothoracic surgery, Heart and Lung transplantation, respiratory conditions, burns and plastics, cancer and breast surgery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a well organised, hardworking dietitian with excellent communication skills and who enjoys working with people. If this is you; apply now!&lt;/p&gt;
